• Initially, Ukraine was the main target of this malware, but later, it affected over
500,000 routers in more than 54 countries worldwide.
• This malware was based on the man-in-the-middle (MITM) cyberattack.
• It maintains its presence on the routers even the router is rebooted.
• It is also known as the Internet of Things (IoT) attack. According to the FBI
reports, VPNFilter malware was spread by a Russian group named Fancy Bear.
• It affects the IoT routers and network-attached storage (NAS) via multistage
infections.
• The first Ukraine blackout in 2015 also used the first-stage malware of this new
format of cyberattack.
